id: pm-jcvg
title: Complete public linked-resource SDK primitives and actionable dependency governance
description: "Finish the remaining pm-zwpp S2/S3/S4 slices as one broad implementation: promote files/docs link orchestration and dependency mutation/inspection behind typed public SDK primitives, repoint CLI presentation handlers away from command-owned domain logic, preserve all discovery and referential-integrity behavior, and make pm-2ler active-versus-legacy dangling dependency reporting consume the same dependency semantics."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: architecture,"area:governance","area:links","area:sdk"
created_at: "2026-07-13T09:59:04.847Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T11:13:04.126Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-13T10:35:51.337Z"
author: codex-sdk-wide-20260713
estimated_minutes: 420
acceptance_criteria: "Public typed SDK primitives own files/docs/deps orchestration and are exported through the package; CLI files/docs/deps handlers are thin presentation layers over those primitives; active and legacy dangling dependency references are separately reported with no remediation that mutates terminal items; CLI JSON/TOON behavior remains compatible; docstrings and SDK docs are complete; focused tests, full 100/100/100/100 coverage, strict quality/security gates, installed-package temp-project proof, changelog generation, and review/merge validation pass."
parent: pm-zwpp
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: "Promoted linked-artifact, files, docs, and dependency orchestration into typed public SDK modules; routed runtime consumers through SDK primitives; removed 34 private CLI-to-core imports; documented and verified packed consumption."
expected_result: "Public SDK owns linked-resource and dependency primitives while CLI behavior, strict quality, exact coverage, and installed-package behavior remain compatible."
actual_result: "CLI files/docs/deps are thin SDK re-exports; direct SDK and PmClient consumers pass; 5,604 tests pass at 100/100/100/100; static/docs/contracts/security/package/Sentry gates pass."
